x'-Ax=Bu(t)
e^{(t_0-t)A}
e^{(t_0-t)A}(x'-Ax)=e^{(t_0-t)A}Bu(t)\implies \dfrac{d}{dt}e^{(t_0-t)A}x=e^{(t_0-t)A}Bu(t)
\int_{t_0}^{t}\dfrac{d}{ds}e^{(t_0-s)A}xds=\int_{t_0}^te^{(t_0-s)A}Bu(s)ds
 x(t) = e^{A(t-t_0)}x_0 + \int_{t_0}^t e^{A(t_0-s)}Bu(s)ds. 
